  "prompt": "Who are IAS Aspirants?",
  "response": "IAS Aspirants are individuals who are preparing to become Indian Administrative Service (IAS) officers by attempting the Civil Services Examination conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC). Key characteristics of IAS aspirants include:\n\n1. Educational Background\n- Usually graduates from various disciplines\n- Often from top universities and colleges\n- Academic backgrounds in humanities, science, engineering, or commerce\n\n2. Age Criteria\n- Generally between 21-32 years old\n- Age relaxations for certain categories as per government norms\n\n3. Examination Preparation\n- Study for UPSC Civil Services Examination\n- Prepare for three stages:\n  a) Preliminary Examination\n  b) Main Examination\n  c) Personal Interview\n\n4. Common Characteristics\n- Highly motivated\n- Strong academic background\n- Deep interest in public service\n- Commitment to nation-building\n- Persistent and hardworking\n- Good analytical and communication skills\n\n5. Preparation Strategy\n- Extensive reading\n- Current affairs knowledge\n- Optional subject preparation\n- Mock tests and previous year question papers\n- Coaching or self-study\n\nIAS aspirants aim to become prestigious government administrators responsible for implementing policies and managing government operations at various levels.",
